####  URM-40LC EW  ####

1. install driver according to your ubuntu version
  #sudo apt-get install ros-kinetic-urg-node

2. if you are the uper version than kinetic, go to https://github.com/ros-drivers/urg_node to    download this package and put into your package.

3. go to your workspace /src/urg_node/launch/urg_lidar.launch to set your IP
  <param name="ip_address" value="192.168.0.10"/>

4. set ethernet usb IP different with 192.168.0.10


####  UTM-30LX  ####

1. install driver according to your ubuntu version
  #sudo apt-get install ros-kinetic-urg-node
2. if you are the uper version than kinetic, go to https://github.com/ros-drivers/urg_node to
download this package and put into your package.
3. give your ttyACM the highest permission 
  sudo chmod 777 /dev/ttyACMx
4. forever give the permission for this device
  ## make the rules
  cd /etc/udev/rules.d
  ##mkdir 99-hokuyo.rules
  sudo vim 99-hokuyo.rules
  ## add the following code in 99-hokuyo.rules
  KERNEL=="ttyACM[0-9]*", ACTION=="add", ATTRS{idVendor}=="15d1", MODE="0666", GROUP="dialout", SYMLINK+="sensors/hokuyo"
  ## check the permission of your device
  ls -l /dev/sensors/hokuyo
  




